A vintage 1970s-style technical illustration showing layers of computing evolution: at the bottom, an old green-phosphor terminal monitor with command lines, rising through middle layers of circuit boards and database symbols, transforming into modern server racks at the top, all connected by flowing data streams rendered as glowing amber and green ribbons. The composition has a warm sepia-toned palette with touches of forest green, suggesting environmental themes. Aged paper texture overlays the entire image, with subtle coffee stains at the corners. The aesthetic evokes retro technical manuals and architectural blueprints from the 1980s, celebrating two decades of software evolution from terminal applications to web-based systems.
